@page
@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Disclaimer - Zariya";
}
<section class="py-5 text-center" style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, #FFF5F5 0%, #FFF0F0 100%);">
    <div class="container py-4">
        <span class="badge bg-danger mb-3 px-3 py-2 text-uppercase" style="border-radius: 30px; letter-spacing: 1px; font-weight: 700; font-size: 0.75rem;">Legal Notice</span>
        <h1 class="display-4 fw-bold text-dark mb-3">Disclaimer</h1>
        <p class="lead text-muted mx-auto" style="max-width: 600px; font-size: 1.1rem;">
            Please read this medical and general disclaimer carefully before utilizing the Zariya platform.
        </p>
    </div>
</section>
<div class="container py-5" style="max-width: 900px;">
    <div class="card border-0 shadow-sm p-5" style="border-radius: 20px;">
        <div class="alert alert-warning mb-5 d-flex gap-3 align-items-start" style="border-radius: 12px;">
            <i class="fas fa-exclamation-triangle fa-lg mt-1 text-warning"></i>
            <div>
                <strong>Critical Medical Notice:</strong> Zariya is NOT a medical service provider, blood bank, or healthcare facility. We do not perform laboratory testing, cross-matching, or blood extraction.
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="mb-5">
            <h2 class="h4 fw-bold text-danger mb-3"><i class="fas fa-stethoscope me-2"></i>1. No Medical Advice or Diagnostics</h2>
            <p class="text-muted" style="line-height: 1.8;">
                All content, guidelines, FAQs, and reports found on Zariya are for general informational purposes only. The information does not constitute medical advice, diagnosis, or treatment protocols. Always seek the advice of your physician or other qualified health providers with any questions you may have regarding a medical condition or blood compatibility.
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class="mb-5">
            <h2 class="h4 fw-bold text-danger mb-3"><i class="fas fa-check-double me-2"></i>2. Responsibility for Blood Compatibility Testing</h2>
            <p class="text-muted" style="line-height: 1.8;">
                Zariya merely acts as an intermediary directory to connect willing volunteers with people in need. It is the <strong>absolute and sole responsibility</strong> of the recipient, their caretakers, and the receiving hospital or laboratory to perform all necessary blood grouping, screening, infectious disease testing, and cross-matching before any transfusion takes place. Zariya does not warrant that the blood provided by any volunteer is safe or compatible.
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class="mb-5">
            <h2 class="h4 fw-bold text-danger mb-3"><i class="fas fa-user-check me-2"></i>3. Accuracy of Donor Information</h2>
            <p class="text-muted" style="line-height: 1.8;">
                Although we verify donor CNICs and support complaint tracking to filter malicious profiles, donor listings are generated based on voluntary self-reporting. Zariya cannot guarantee that the name, age, blood type, availability, or health history of any registered user is entirely accurate, up to date, or complete.
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class="mb-5">
            <h2 class="h4 fw-bold text-danger mb-3"><i class="fas fa-hands-helping me-2"></i>4. Voluntary & Unpaid Nature</h2>
            <p class="text-muted" style="line-height: 1.8;">
                Zariya is a free service. We strongly advise users against paying any money or compensation to donors found through our platform. If anyone requests money, please file a complaint immediately via your dashboard. Zariya is not responsible for any financial losses or extortion attempts committed by third parties.
            </p>
        </div>
        <div>
            <h2 class="h4 fw-bold text-danger mb-3"><i class="fas fa-balance-scale me-2"></i>5. Limitation of Liability</h2>
            <p class="text-muted" style="line-height: 1.8;">
                Under no circumstances shall Zariya, its developers, or affiliates be liable for any direct, indirect, incidental, or consequential damages, medical complications, infections, transfusion reactions, or death resulting from the use or inability to use this platform, or from any interactions with other users.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>